OL,3,CSmell from wheelie bin was woman's body
OL,5,FThe court heard Ms Jordan had been
OL,6,Fpartying with another woman at
OL,7,FMetcalf's home on the night of 11 June.
OL,9,FThe two women had an argument with
OL,10,FMetcalfe and left, but Ms Jordan
OL,11,Freturned later.
OL,13,FWhile the circumstances of her death
OL,14,Fremain unclear, Ms Jordan was later
OL,15,Fstripped naked and stuffed in a
OL,16,Fwheelie bin, where she remained in
OL,17,FMetcalfe's yard for several days.
OL,19,FWhen neighbours complained of the
OL,20,Fsmell, he dumped the body outside the
OL,21,Fstore on Kimberley Road.
